The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Suicide in river

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Thirty two-year-old Binoy Bagaria committed suicide by jumping from Howrah bridge on Sunday morning. 

 Officer-in-charge of River Traffic Police Deepak Chatterjee said Bagaria was a resident of Hemchandra Naskar Road, in Beleghata. 

 He came to the bridge from his house on a motorcycle, parked the vehicle on the Calcutta side of the bridge and then jumped into the river.

 Preliminary investigation has revealed Binoy had an altercation with his wife before he decided to kill himself. The River Traffic Police is searching for the body. A missing persons diary has been lodged with North Port police station.




